Function to merge two lists and find the minimum value
def merge_and_find_min(list1, list2):
     Merge the two lists
    merged_list = list1 + list2
Find the minimum value in the merged list
    min_value = min(merged_list)
 return merged_list, min_value
 Example lists
list1 = [3, 7, 1, 9]
list2 = [5, 2, 8, 4]
 Call the function to merge the lists and find the minimum value
merged_list, min_value = merge_and_find_min(list1, list2)
Print the merged list and the minimum value
print("Merged List:", merged_list)
print("Minimum Value:", min_value)
